  <h2>Why this block matters</h2>
  <p class="sub">First defense of the year. The room is on your side.</p>
  <p>Today is the first of the eight defenses you'll give across the year. 5-minute pitch + 2-minute Q&amp;A; ~10-12 students perform live and the rest deliver in alt format that gets reviewed asynchronously. The point isn't perfection — it's the rep. You'll have seven more after this. Use today to learn what you sound like under questioning.</p>
  <p>The unit closes with a reflection on what you learned about how <em>you</em> think (not what you learned about contested topics) and a preview of Unit 1. Unit 1 will use the OPVL muscle you just built — same framework, applied to planetary science sources.</p>
</section>

