<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">🛠️ Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — the defenses themselves</h2>
  <p class="sub">No choice board today. The block runs on a roster: ~10-12 students deliver live defenses; everyone else either delivers in alt format (asynchronous review) or sits as panelist-observer for at least one live defense.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> I can deliver my defense in the format I chose, answer at least one panelist question, and name one thing about my AI use I would change next time.
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">A</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Live defense (5-min pitch + 2-min Q&amp;A)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">You're on the roster for today. Set up, deliver, answer questions. Panelists are 2-3 peers + Mr. Ignash. Stay on the panel after for at least one other student's defense.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Live</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">B</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Panelist-observer</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">If you're not delivering live today, sit as a panelist for at least one defense. Use the observation guide to give the speaker specific, rubric-aligned feedback. This counts as participation.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Group · Default</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">C</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Alt-format finalisation</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">If your defense is in video or written-response form, today is the day to finalise and submit. Capacity for live re-record is in the quiet corner if you need a second take.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Alt</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

