  <span class="section-tag">🔭 Preview — Unit 1</span>
  <h2>Where we go next</h2>
  <p>Unit 1 asks: <strong>what makes a planet habitable?</strong> Same OPVL muscle, applied to planetary-science sources (NASA data, exoplanet detection papers, atmospheric chemistry textbook chapters). You'll write the <em>Goldilocks Report</em> and defend your habitability framework against a NASA-committee panel. Same defense format you just survived — just with a new topic and slightly more technical sources.</p>
  <p>The framework you built this unit (OPVL + AI Documentation Protocol) doesn't get retaught. It gets used. The <strong>[U0 Anchor Article — TBD pending librarian]</strong> you OPVL'd in Blocks 2 + 3 is also still relevant — <a href="/units/unit-1/block-1/">U1 Block 1</a> picks it up again as the bridge into habitability work. If something feels shaky from Unit 0, the <a href="/foundations/">Foundations</a> pages stay live all year.</p>
